{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/cambium\/gettingstarted"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium"],["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium\/CalculatorExample"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium\/GettingStarted","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Cambium"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"Getting Started"},"abstract":[{"text":"Build your first Cambium tree by writing a tiny calculator parser.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you’re looking at Cambium, you’re probably writing a parser and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"considering using concrete syntax trees as its output. We’ll walk"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"through a complete example from defining a language all the way to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"walking the resulting tree."}]},{"name":"Tip","type":"aside","style":"tip","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This article is a narrative skim of Cambium’s API. For a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"hands-on, step-by-step build of a more substantial calculator with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"precedence, error recovery, incremental reparse, witness-driven"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"analysis caches, parallel evaluation, and serialization — see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/TableOfContents","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We’ll support addition and subtraction on integers, with parentheses"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for grouping. The user is allowed to write nested expressions like"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1-(2+5)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The full pipeline:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Define an enumeration of the kinds of tokens (like keywords) and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"nodes (like “an expression”) that you want in your syntax, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conform it to "},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxLanguage","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a "},{"code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and call "},{"code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/startNode(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/token(_:text:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/finishNode()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" from your parser."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Call "},{"code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/finish()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to obtain a "},{"code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenBuildResult","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"then call "},{"code":"result.snapshot.makeSyntaxTree()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to get a "},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxTree","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you can traverse."}]}]}]},{"anchor":"Defining-the-language","level":2,"text":"Defining the language","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"First, list the different parts of your grammar. We use a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UInt32"},{"type":"text","text":"-backed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"enum and let the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@CambiumSyntaxKind"},{"type":"text","text":" macro derive every requirement"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxKind"},{"type":"text","text":" for us. Operators and parentheses always render to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the same text, so we mark them with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@StaticText"},{"type":"text","text":"; integers vary"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"between occurrences and stay un-annotated."}]},{"code":["import Cambium","import CambiumSyntaxMacros","","@CambiumSyntaxKind","enum CalcKind: UInt32, Sendable {","    \/\/ Tokens","    case integer = 1","    @StaticText(\"+\") case plus = 2","    @StaticText(\"-\") case minus = 3","    @StaticText(\"(\") case lparen = 4","    @StaticText(\")\") case rparen = 5","    @StaticText(\" \") case whitespace = 6","","    \/\/ Nodes","    case expr = 100","    case root = 101","","    \/\/ Sentinels for missing\/error recovery","    case missing = 200","    case error = 201","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Next we tie the kind enum to a language type. Most of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxLanguage","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" requirements have default implementations that work"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for any "},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxKind","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"-conforming enum, so the conformance is short:"}]},{"code":["enum Calc: SyntaxLanguage {","    typealias Kind = CalcKind","","    static let rootKind: CalcKind = .root","    static let missingKind: CalcKind = .missing","    static let errorKind: CalcKind = .error","","    \/\/ Stable IDs in case we ever serialize trees.","    static let serializationID = \"com.example.calc\"","    static let serializationVersion: UInt32 = 1","","    \/\/ Trivia and node\/token classification.","    static func isTrivia(_ kind: CalcKind) -> Bool {","        kind == .whitespace","    }","","    static func isNode(_ kind: CalcKind) -> Bool {","        switch kind {","        case .expr, .root, .missing, .error:","            return true","        default:","            return false","        }","    }","","    static func isToken(_ kind: CalcKind) -> Bool {","        !isNode(kind)","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That’s everything Cambium needs to specialize its generic types for our"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"language. Override "},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxLanguage\/isNode(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxLanguage\/isToken(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" when your language has dynamic-text token"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"kinds like "},{"code":"integer","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"; the default classifier treats static-text kinds as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tokens and non-static kinds as nodes."}]},{"anchor":"Parsing-into-a-green-tree","level":2,"text":"Parsing into a green tree","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For the purposes of this introduction, assume there is a lexer that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"yields the following tokens:"}]},{"code":["enum Token: Equatable {","    \/\/ Number strings are not yet parsed into actual numbers; we","    \/\/ remember the slice of the input that contains their digits.","    case integer(String)","    case plus","    case minus","    case lparen","    case rparen","    case eof","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A simple "},{"code":"Lexer","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" over a "},{"code":"String","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is part of the example flow but we"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"won’t show it inline; whatever lexer you have works fine as long as it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"yields "},{"code":"Token","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s in source order. To keep the parser short, these"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"snippets skip whitespace; a production CST parser should append trivia"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tokens such as "},{"code":".whitespace","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to keep the tree fully lossless."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Let’s wire the lexer up to a parser"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that owns a "},{"code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"code":["struct Parser {","    private var lexer: Lexer","    private var builder: GreenTreeBuilder<Calc>","","    init(input: String) {","        self.lexer = Lexer(input: input)","        self.builder = GreenTreeBuilder<Calc>()","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In contrast to parsers that return abstract syntax trees, with Cambium"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the syntax tree nodes for every element of the language grammar have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the same type: "},{"code":"CambiumCore\/GreenNode","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for the inner (“green”) tree and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeCursor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (with optional "},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeHandle","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" projection)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the outer (“red”) tree. Different kinds of nodes and tokens are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"differentiated by their kind tag."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can implement many types of parsers with Cambium. To get a feel for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"how it works, consider a recursive-descent parser. With a more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"traditional AST one would define different AST structs for each"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"syntactic category and have parsing functions return the matching AST"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"type. Because Cambium’s syntax trees are untyped, there is no explicit"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"AST representation that the parser would build. Instead, parsing into"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a CST using the builder follows the source code more closely: you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tell Cambium about each new element you enter and every token the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parser consumes."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The most trivial example is the root parser entry point, which just","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"opens a root node containing the whole expression and finishes it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"again:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["extension Parser {","    mutating func parse() throws {","        builder.startNode(.root)","        try parseExpr()","        try builder.finishNode()","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"As there isn’t a static AST type to return, the parser is very","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"flexible as to what is part of a node. If the user is editing a struct","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and has not yet typed a field’s type, the CST node for the struct","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"doesn’t care that its child slot is empty. Similarly, leftover","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"identifiers from a half-deleted field can be a part of the struct","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"node without any modifications to the syntax tree definition. This","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"property is the key to why CSTs are such a good fit as a lossless","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"input representation, which necessitates the syntax tree to mirror the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"user-specific layout of whitespace and comments around the AST items.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Speculative-wrapping-with-checkpoints","level":3,"text":"Speculative wrapping with checkpoints","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In our calculator we have to deal with the fact that, when we see a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"number, the parser doesn’t yet know whether more operations follow."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"That is, in the expression "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1 + 2"},{"type":"text","text":", the parser only knows it’s looking"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at a binary operation once it sees the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+"},{"type":"text","text":". The event-like model of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"building trees in Cambium implies that when reaching the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+"},{"type":"text","text":", the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parser would already need to have entered a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CalcKind.expr"},{"type":"text","text":" node"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the whole input to be part of the expression."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To get around this, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder"},{"type":"text","text":" provides"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/checkpoint()"},{"type":"text","text":", which we can call to “remember” the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"current builder position. Later, when the parser sees the following"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+"},{"type":"text","text":", it can wrap everything since the checkpoint inside an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CalcKind.expr"},{"type":"text","text":" node using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/startNode(at:_:)"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"code":["extension Parser {","    mutating func parseLhs() throws {","        switch try lexer.peek() {","        case .integer(let n):","            _ = try lexer.next()","            try builder.token(.integer, text: n)","","        case .lparen:","            \/\/ Wrap the grouped expression inside a node containing it","            \/\/ and its parentheses.","            builder.startNode(.expr)","            _ = try lexer.next()","            try builder.staticToken(.lparen)","            try parseExpr()","            guard case .rparen = try lexer.next() else {","                throw ParseError.missingRParen","            }","            try builder.staticToken(.rparen)","            try builder.finishNode()","","        case .eof:","            throw ParseError.unexpectedEOF","","        case let other:","            throw ParseError.unexpectedToken(other)","        }","    }","","    mutating func parseExpr() throws {","        \/\/ Remember our current position.","        let beforeExpr = builder.checkpoint()","","        \/\/ Parse the start of the expression.","        try parseLhs()","","        \/\/ Check whether the expression continues with `+ <more>` or","        \/\/ `- <more>`.","        let nextToken = try lexer.peek()","        let opKind: CalcKind","        switch nextToken {","        case .plus:  opKind = .plus","        case .minus: opKind = .minus","        case .rparen, .eof: return","        case let other:","            throw ParseError.unexpectedToken(other)","        }","","        \/\/ If so, retroactively wrap the (already parsed) LHS and the","        \/\/ following RHS inside an `expr` node.","        try builder.startNode(at: beforeExpr, .expr)","        _ = try lexer.next()","        try builder.staticToken(opKind)","        try parseExpr() \/\/ RHS","        try builder.finishNode()","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Static-text-and-dynamic-text-tokens","level":3,"text":"Static-text and dynamic-text tokens","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Notice the split between","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/token(_:text:)"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/staticToken(_:)"},{"text":", and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/missingToken(_:)"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/staticToken(_:)"},{"text":" only works on kinds whose","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxLanguage\/staticText(for:)"},{"text":" returns non-","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":". The text comes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from the language definition; you don’t have to repeat it at the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"call site.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/token(_:text:)"},{"text":" only works on kinds with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"no"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" static text — typically identifiers and literals. The supplied","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"string is interned in the builder’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenNodeCache"},{"text":", so two","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"occurrences of the same identifier dedupe to one allocation.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/missingToken(_:)"},{"text":" records a parser-recovered","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"placeholder. It always renders to nothing.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/largeToken(_:text:)"},{"text":" is the right choice for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"inherently unique payloads like long string literals, where","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"hash-interning would only waste hash work.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Mixing them up — for example, calling ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"token(.plus, text: \"+\")"},{"text":" —","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"throws ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilderError\/staticKindRequiresStaticToken(_:)"},{"text":" so","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"schema mistakes are caught at the call site instead of producing a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"silently malformed tree.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Obtaining-the-parser-result","level":2,"text":"Obtaining the parser result","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Our parser can now parse our little arithmetic language, but its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"methods don’t return anything. Where does the syntax tree come from?","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The answer is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/finish()"},{"text":", which finally consumes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the builder and returns a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenBuildResult"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"code":["extension Parser {","    consuming func finish() throws -> GreenBuildResult<Calc> {","        try builder.finish()","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The result includes the green ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenBuildResult\/root"},{"text":", the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenBuildResult\/resolver"},{"text":" (sealed once at ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"finish()"},{"text":" via the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"interner’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/TokenInterner\/makeResolver()"},{"text":"), and the underlying","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeContext"},{"text":" (accessible via","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenBuildResult\/intoContext()"},{"text":"). The context bundles the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"interner with the cache as a namespace-bound unit; pass it to the next","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"builder via ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder\/init(context:)"},{"text":" to keep","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"token-key namespace identity stable across reparses.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To work with the syntax tree, materialize a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxTree"},{"text":" from the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"build result’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenBuildResult\/snapshot"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"code":["let input = \"11+2-(5+4)\"","var parser = Parser(input: input)","try parser.parse()","","let result = try parser.finish()","let tree = result.snapshot.makeSyntaxTree()"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"tree"},{"text":" is a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~Copyable"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxTree"},{"text":". To traverse it, hand a closure","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxTree\/withRoot(_:)"},{"text":"; the closure receives a borrowed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeCursor"},{"text":" on the root.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Traversing-the-tree","level":2,"text":"Traversing the tree","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The cursor API mirrors how you’d write a recursive-descent walker, but","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"without the per-node allocations. Borrow-on-demand instead of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"return [Cursor]"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"code":["tree.withRoot { root in","    print(\"root kind: \\(Calc.name(for: root.kind))\")","    print(\"root range: \\(root.textRange)\")","","    root.forEachChild { child in","        print(\" child: \\(Calc.name(for: child.kind)) \\(child.textRange)\")","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For a depth-first walk over every descendant:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["tree.withRoot { root in","    _ = root.visitPreorder { node in","        \/\/ Return .skipChildren or .stop to control descent.","        print(\"\\(Calc.name(for: node.kind)) \\(node.textRange)\")","        return .continue","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For a token-aware walk (most editor scenarios), use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeCursor\/walkPreorderWithTokens(_:)"},{"text":" or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeCursor\/tokens(in:_:)"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Reading-text-without-allocating","level":3,"text":"Reading text without allocating","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Materializing source text as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"text":" is occasionally what you want","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeCursor\/makeString()"},{"text":"), but for hot-path scans prefer the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"borrowed text view:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["tree.withRoot { root in","    root.withText { text in","        if text.contains(0x2B) { \/\/ '+'","            \/\/ ...","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxText"},{"text":" walks the green tree on demand and yields chunks","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"straight from the resolver’s interned bytes — no copies, no","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"allocations unless you ask for a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Promoting-to-a-copyable-Sendable-tree","level":3,"text":"Promoting to a copyable, Sendable tree","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyntaxTree"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~Copyable"},{"text":" so traversal stays unambiguous about","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"ownership. When you need to publish a tree to SwiftUI, hand it to a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Task"},{"text":", or store it in a long-lived snapshot, promote it to a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SharedSyntaxTree"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"code":["let shared = tree.intoShared()","","\/\/ Sendable across actors, retained until the last reference is gone.","await Task.detached {","    shared.withRoot { root in","        \/\/ ... background work","    }","}.value"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For long-lived references to ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"specific nodes","type":"text"}]},{"text":", use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SharedSyntaxTree\/rootHandle()"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeCursor\/makeHandle()"},{"text":" to obtain copyable","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeHandle"},{"text":" values that you can store in dictionaries,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"attach diagnostics to, or send across actors.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Editing-a-tree","level":2,"text":"Editing a tree","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Trees are persistent. To “edit” one, call","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SharedSyntaxTree.replacing(_:with:context:)"},{"text":" with the handle of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"node to replace and a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/ResolvedGreenNode"},{"text":" (or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeSnapshot"},{"text":", or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenBuildResult"},{"text":")","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of the replacement. The result is a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/ReplacementResult"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with the new tree and a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/ReplacementWitness"},{"text":" describing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the structural change. The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context:"},{"text":" argument is a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeContext"},{"text":" whose interner shares the target","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tree’s namespace — pass ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"result.intoContext()"},{"text":" from the build that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"produced the target tree to keep namespace identity intact.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["let original = tree.intoShared()","","\/\/ Build a replacement subtree, reusing the original's context so the","\/\/ replacement's keys land in the same namespace.","var rebuilder = GreenTreeBuilder<Calc>(context: result.intoContext())","rebuilder.startNode(.expr)","try rebuilder.token(.integer, text: \"42\")","try rebuilder.finishNode()","let replacement = try rebuilder.finish()","let replacementSnapshot = replacement.snapshot","","\/\/ Decide which node to replace — for example, the root's first child.","let target: SyntaxNodeHandle<Calc> = original.withRoot { root in","    root.withFirstChild { $0.makeHandle() }!","}","","var context = replacement.intoContext()","let edit = try original.replacing(target, with: replacementSnapshot, context: &context)","let witness = edit.witness","let next = edit.intoTree()"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Inspect ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"witness"},{"text":" to translate any v0 references (handles you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"held before the edit) into v1: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"witness.classify(path:)"},{"text":" returns a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/ReplacementOutcome"},{"text":" telling you whether the path is unchanged, an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"ancestor of the edit, the replaced node itself, or a descendant of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the deleted region.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Incremental-parsing","level":2,"text":"Incremental parsing","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For an editor that reparses on every keystroke, you don’t want to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"discard the entire tree each time. The CambiumIncremental module","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"provides:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/ParseInput"},{"text":" — the bundle of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"(textUTF8, edits, previousTree)"},{"text":" your","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parser receives for each parse pass.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/IncrementalParseSession"},{"text":" — long-lived state that aggregates","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reuse counters and an accepted-reuse log across parses.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/ReuseOracle"},{"text":" — the parser-facing interface that offers candidate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"subtrees from the previous tree at given offsets.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/ParseWitness"},{"text":" — the post-parse summary: which subtrees were","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"carried over by reference, which regions were freshly parsed.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A typical reparse loop:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["let session = IncrementalParseSession<Calc>()","var sharedTree: SharedSyntaxTree<Calc>? = nil","","\/\/ On each edit:","let input = ParseInput<Calc>(text: newText, edits: edits, previousTree: sharedTree)","let oracle = session.makeReuseOracle(for: input)","","\/\/ Inside your parser, before parsing a node of kind .expr at an old-tree","\/\/ offset that survived edit invalidation:","let accepted = try oracle.withReusableNode(startingAt: oldExprStart, kind: .expr) { reusable in","    \/\/ Capture the witness data before the borrowed cursor leaves scope.","    let oldPath = reusable.childIndexPath()","    let green = reusable.green { $0 }","","    \/\/ Splice the reused subtree into the new tree without re-parsing it.","    try builder.reuseSubtree(reusable)","","    \/\/ The parser\/integrator owns new-path bookkeeping because it knows","    \/\/ where this node is being appended in the output tree.","    return Reuse(green: green, oldPath: oldPath, newPath: newExprPath)","}","","if let accepted {","    session.recordAcceptedReuse(","        oldPath: accepted.oldPath,","        newPath: accepted.newPath,","        green: accepted.green","    )","}","","let result = try builder.finish()","sharedTree = result.snapshot.makeSyntaxTree().intoShared()","","let witness = ParseWitness(","    oldRoot: input.previousTree?.rootGreen,","    newRoot: result.root,","    reusedSubtrees: session.consumeAcceptedReuses()",")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The witness is the right anchor for higher-layer identity tracking:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"diagnostics, selections, fold state, anything attached to nodes by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"identity. Cambium does not maintain those mappings itself — it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"provides the structural primitive and lets you compose the policy","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"appropriate for your editor.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Analysis-sidecars","level":2,"text":"Analysis sidecars","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"CambiumAnalysis provides two per-node sidecar shapes. Use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumAnalysis\/SyntaxMetadataStore"},{"text":" for multi-typed annotations during a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"single analysis pass, and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumAnalysis\/ExternalAnalysisCache"},{"text":" for one","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"long-lived, single-typed memoization cache that can bulk-evict old tree","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"versions.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["let metadata = SyntaxMetadataStore<Calc>()","let typeKey = SyntaxDataKey<String>(\"com.example.calc.value-kind\")","metadata.set(\"integer\", for: typeKey, on: exprHandle)","","let values = ExternalAnalysisCache<Calc, Int64>()","let key = AnalysisCacheKey(","    identity: exprHandle.identity,","    namespace: \"com.example.calc.eval\"",")","values.set(42, for: key)","values.removeValues(notMatching: latestTree.treeID)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Both stores key nodes by ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeIdentity"},{"text":". If you want cached","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"values to survive an incremental reparse, consume ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/ParseWitness"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"records before evicting: translate entries whose old paths fall inside reused","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"subtrees onto the corresponding new paths, then call","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumAnalysis\/ExternalAnalysisCache\/removeValues(notMatching:)"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyntaxDataKey"},{"text":" equality is based on its string name, not its ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Value"},{"text":" type; use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"namespaced strings so unrelated passes do not accidentally share the same slot.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"AST-Layer","level":2,"text":"AST Layer","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"While Cambium is built for concrete syntax trees, applications often","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"want to work with either a CST or an AST representation, or freely","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"switch between them. The CambiumASTSupport module gives you the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"minimal vocabulary to do this: define one ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumASTSupport\/TypedSyntaxNode"},{"text":"-conforming","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"type per AST kind, then use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeHandle\/asTyped(_:)"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxNodeCursor\/withTyped(_:_:)"},{"text":" to safely down-cast generic","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"nodes.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["enum ExprNode: TypedSyntaxNode {","    typealias Lang = Calc","    static let rawKind = Calc.rawKind(for: .expr)","}","","if let exprHandle = nodeHandle.asTyped(ExprNode.self) {","    exprHandle.withCursor { exprCursor in","        \/\/ ... statically known to be an expr","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A grammar-specific layer (likely generated by tooling) is the right","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"place to define one spec type per kind, with kind-specific accessors","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"built on top. Cambium does not ship grammar generators in core — the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumASTSupport\/TypedSyntaxNode","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" protocol is the contract that an AST overlay","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"should target.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"License","level":2,"text":"License","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cambium is distributed under the same dual MIT \/ Apache-2.0 license as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the upstream ","type":"text"},{"code":"cstree","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" it draws inspiration from.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"article","sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"references":{"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/TableOfContents":{"url":"\/tutorials\/tableofcontents","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Cambium is a Swift-native concrete syntax tree library. This"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tutorial series walks you through building a small but"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"production-shaped calculator language end-to-end: a recursive-"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"descent parser that produces a lossless tree, a typed AST overlay,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"an evaluator with memoized analysis, persistent edits with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"identity-preserving witnesses, an incremental reparse loop, fork-"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"join evaluation across structured-concurrent tasks, parallel"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parsing with externalized interning, and on-disk serialization."}],"kind":"overview","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/TableOfContents","title":"Build a Calculator with Cambium","role":"overview"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/documentation/Cambium":{"type":"topic","title":"Cambium","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Swift-native concrete syntax tree library inspired by Rust’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/domenicquirl\/cstree"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/cambium","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium"},"https://github.com/domenicquirl/cstree":{"title":"cstree","type":"link","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/domenicquirl\/cstree","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/domenicquirl\/cstree","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cstree"}]},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/documentation/Cambium/CalculatorExample":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium\/CalculatorExample","type":"topic","title":"Calculator","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/cambium\/calculatorexample","abstract":[{"text":"A complete end-to-end example using Cambium to parse, traverse, edit,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and evaluate a small arithmetic language.","type":"text"}],"role":"sampleCode"}}}